                      "content":  {
                                      "title":  "Will â€” four main uses",
                                      "body":  "WILL + base verb has four important uses:\n\n1. PREDICTIONS (general, based on belief/knowledge)\nâ€¢ Electric vehicles will be everywhere in 10 years.\nâ€¢ She\u0027ll be a great doctor â€” she works so hard.\n\n2. SPONTANEOUS DECISIONS (decided at the moment of speaking)\nâ€¢ [Phone rings] I\u0027ll get it!\nâ€¢ [Friend is struggling] I\u0027ll help you carry that.\n\n3. OFFERS\nâ€¢ I\u0027ll make tea. You rest.\nâ€¢ Shall I carry that for you? / I\u0027ll carry that.\n\n4. PROMISES\nâ€¢ I\u0027ll call you as soon as I reach.\nâ€¢ I won\u0027t tell anyone â€” I promise.",
                                      "grammar_note":  "will + base verb (all persons: I/you/he/she/we/they)\nShort form: I\u0027ll, you\u0027ll, she\u0027ll, we\u0027ll, they\u0027ll\nNegative: won\u0027t (= will not)"
                                  }
                  },
                  {
                      "task_id":  "t1003_02",
